DP  - 2014 Fall
TI  - Mindful mood balance: a case report of Web-based treatment of residual depressive 
      symptoms.
PG  - 58-62
LID - 10.7812/TPP/14-019 [doi]
AB  - Residual depressive symptoms are associated with increased risk for relapse and 
      impaired functioning. Although there is no definitive treatment for residual 
      depressive symptoms, Mindfulness-Based Cognitive Therapy has been shown to be 
      effective, but access is limited. Mindful Mood Balance (MMB), a Web-based 
      adaptation of Mindfulness-Based Cognitive Therapy, was designed to address this 
      care gap. In this case study, we describe a composite case that is representative 
      of the course of intervention with MMB and its implementation in a large 
      integrated delivery system. Specifically, we describe the content of each of 
      eight weekly sessions, and the self-management skills developed by participating 
      in this program. MMB may be a cost-effective and scalable option in primary care 
      for increasing access to treatments for patients with residual depressive 
      symptoms.
